<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4212> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4212" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Defeated and put to death by Pompey in Africa. See 82, Promagistrates, and below, on Pompey." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4157> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4157" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "No title preserved. He escaped to Africa, and assembled a force of Marians there (Plut. Pomp. 10.1; 11.1; cf. Cic. Leg. Man. 30; Liv. Per. 89; Eutrop. 5.9.1; Oros. 5.24.16; Schol. Bob. 138, and Schol. Gron. 320 Stangl). See below, on Fabius Hadrianus; and 81, Promagistrates." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4156> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4156" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "7 As the Marians continued to hold Africa after the death of Fabius Hadrianus and Carbo escaped there before going to Sicily, it is probable that Domitius Ahenobarbus was already in Africa in 82 before the lists of the proscribed were published." .
